#### INSTALL OF LATEST CMAKE

1. Uninstall the default version provided by Ubuntu's package manager:

   ```sudo apt-get purge cmake```

2. Go to the official [CMake website](https://cmake.org/download/) and download and 
   extract the latest version (v.3.10.2 at time of writing). Update the version and build variables using the following commands to get the desired veriion. 


   ```version=3.10```   
   ```build=2```   
   ```mkdir ~/temp```   
   ```cd ~/temp```   
   ```wget https://cmake.org/files/v$version/cmake-$version.$build.tar.gz```   
   ```tar -xzvf cmake-$version.$build.tar.gz```   
   ```cd cmake-$version.$build/```

3. Install the extracted source by running:

   ```./bootstrap```   
   ```make -j4```   
   ```sudo make install```   

4. Test your new cmake version.

   ```$ cmake --version```   

   ```Results of cmake --version:```   

   ```cmake version 3.10.X```    
